## 4. Replace your current single call with this grouped version

Instead of calling `GetT24FileContentRecordsV2` once for the full list, do this:

```csharp
List<T24FileContentGroup> t24FileContentGroups =
    SplitT24ContentsByDebitAccountAndBeneficiaryIndicator(
        getFileImportByIdRes.FileImport.FileImportContents,
        getFileByIdResponse.File.IsPrivateSector);
```

Then loop over each group:

```csharp
foreach (T24FileContentGroup group in t24FileContentGroups)
{
    List<Dictionary<string, string>> bodyRecords = GetT24FileContentRecordsV2(
        group.FileImportContents,
        getFileByIdResponse.File.CurrencyCode,
        request.PaymentDescription,
        request.ValueDate,
        transactionDate,
        getFileByIdResponse.File.IsPrivateSector);

    DataExportGenerateFileContentResponse responseData =
        GenerateDataExportFileContent(
            request.BaseReq.CorrelationId,
            _globalSettings.GenerateT24FileCode,
            bodyRecords);

    List<Dictionary<string, string>> totalBodyRecords =
        GetT24TotalFileContentRecords(
            getFileByIdResponse.File.InstitutionDescription!,
            group.FileImportContents);

    DataExportGenerateFileContentResponse totalResponseData =
        GenerateDataExportFileContent(
            request.BaseReq.CorrelationId,
            _globalSettings.GenerateT24TotalFileCode,
            totalBodyRecords);
}
```

